- **"show aic last"** — When the user says this (or similar), run Bash with `(grep -q '"devMode": true' aic.config.json 2>/dev/null && pnpm aic last) || npx @jatbas/aic last` from the project directory. Relay stdout byte-for-byte.

- **"show aic projects"** — When the user says this (or similar), run Bash with `(grep -q '"devMode": true' aic.config.json 2>/dev/null && pnpm aic projects) || npx @jatbas/aic projects`. Relay stdout byte-for-byte.

- **"run aic model test"** — When the user says this (or similar), call the `aic_model_test` MCP tool with `{ "projectRoot": "<absolute workspace root>" }`. The tool returns a `probeId`, three challenges, and instructions. Solve challenge 1 (arithmetic) and challenge 2 (string-reverse). Then call `aic_compile` with intent exactly equal to `"model-test-<answer1>-<answer2>"` (replace with your computed answers). Finally call `aic_model_test` again with `{ "projectRoot": "<absolute workspace root>", "probeId": "<probeId from step 1>", "answers": [<arithmetic answer>, "<reversed string>"] }`. Display the result as a table with columns: Test, Result (Pass/Fail), Notes. Start the reply with one short line: **Model test = agent capability probe.**

## Maintenance

- Whenever a **rule** in `.cursor/rules/` is changed or added, review this router: update the context table and/or critical reminders so the map stays accurate.
- **Hooks sync:** Critical reminders above are injected by `.cursor/hooks/AIC-session-init.cjs` at session start. When you edit the critical reminders list, the hook stays in sync automatically (it reads this file). No need to edit hook code unless you change the section heading or structure.
- **Cross-editor sync:** This file and `.claude/CLAUDE.md` are the two canonical rule files. They must stay in sync. Architectural invariants, security rules, dependency rules, commit rules, ESLint rules, and test rules are identical across both. Only editor-specific mechanics differ (hooks vs manual `aic_compile` calls, prompt command wording). Prompt commands use shell `npx @jatbas/aic …` diagnostics, not MCP tool calls. When changing any shared rule, update in one commit: (1) this file, (2) `.claude/CLAUDE.md`, (3) `CLAUDE_MD_TEMPLATE` in `integrations/claude/install.cjs`, and (4) `CLAUDE_MD_TEMPLATE` in `mcp/src/install-trigger-rule.ts` — same bytes; see `AIC-claude-md-managed-section.mdc` (no version banner inside the managed body).
